In his weekly address, President Donald J. Trump discussed the progress made in the six weeks since he took office. He highlighted his recent visit to the soon-to-be commissioned U.S.S. Gerald R. Ford, emphasizing the importance of American military power and the role of aircraft carriers in projecting strength at sea. The President also outlined his vision for national rebuilding, which includes eliminating the defense sequester and investing in the military. He emphasized that investing in the military is an investment in peace and in the men and women who serve in uniform. The President expressed optimism about the opportunities to strengthen the military, reboot the economy, and bring back jobs, calling on Americans to work together and prioritize the country's interests.